The paper focuses on video representation learning and latent concept mining for multi-label video classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as weighted multi-model ensemble and learning with temporal segments, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for concept mining, which is relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL) category.
